      • createTemplateIdentifierField

        public static FastField createTemplateIdentifierField()
        Utility for creating the special field used to encode/decode template identifiers.

        This is an unsigned int32 field using the copy constructor with the global dictionary. It is encoded as a mandatory field despite references to "optional" in the spec.

        "A segment has a header consisting of a Presence Map followed by an optional Template Identifier. ...A template identifier is represented as an Unsigned Integer in the stream. ...A template identifier is encoded as if a copy operator was specified. The operator uses the global dictionary and has an internal key common to all template identifier fields."

        Returns:
        Field representing a template identifier.

      • getDictionaryName

        public IName getDictionaryName()
        Description copied from interface: IField
        Dictionary name as identified by FAST dictionaryAttr, after translation of special "template" and "type" names.

        Note that the name returned is an IName, which means that a namespace may be specified. This will happen if the name was translated from "template" or "type", since templates and types are both identified by namespace aware names.

        This is the dictionary that will apply to the field. It can be inherited. "The dictionary name is specified by the dictionary attribute on the field operator element or where allowed by the schema on ancestor elements. If there are more than one dictionary attribute in the ancestry, the attribute of the nearest element applies. If the attribute is not specified, the global dictionary is used."

        This may return null if no dictionary is specified or inherited.

        Specified by:
        getDictionaryName in interface IField
        Returns:
        Name of applicable dictionary

        public short getInternalKey()
        Description copied from interface: IField
        Internal small int key used to look up dictionary values.

        This is computed and assigned to each field when the template is processed.

        It only needs to be unique for this field's dictionary - not unique across all fields.

      • isAssignedPresenceBit

        public boolean isAssignedPresenceBit()
        Description copied from interface: IField
        True if this field has a bit assigned in the presence map.

        The logic for this is not intuitive. It is described in the FAST specification in the section on PresenceMap's.

        For example:

        • Mandatory fields with a constant operator or no operator do not have a presence bit.
        • Optional fields with no operator do not have a presence bit (they *always* appear in the encoded stream with decoded absence indicated by a NULL value).
        • Fields with delta operators do not have a presence bit.
        Specified by:
        isAssignedPresenceBit in interface IField
        Returns:
        True if this field has a bit assigned in the presence map.
